    <item>
      <title>June 2026 Meeting Cancellation Notice</title>
      <link>https://dav84.us/post/2026-05-15-meeting-cancelled/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 15 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>contact@dav84.us</author>
      <guid>https://dav84.us/post/2026-05-15-meeting-cancelled/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;We would like to inform all members that the June meeting is cancelled.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This cancellation applies only to the June meeting and does not affect any other scheduled gatherings.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;july-meeting-confirmation&#34;&gt;July Meeting Confirmation&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Our July meeting will proceed as previously scheduled at the &lt;strong&gt;same location and the same time&lt;/strong&gt; as previously communicated. Our meeting location will remain a the Crestwood Elks Lodge on the first Friday of the month at 6:30pm. There are no changes to the July meeting venue, date, or start time.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>About</title>
      <link>https://dav84.us/page/about/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>contact@dav84.us</author>
      <guid>https://dav84.us/page/about/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;davs-mission-statement&#34;&gt;DAV’s Mission Statement&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;content-section&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;We are dedicated to a single purpose: empowering veterans to lead high-quality lives with respect and dignity. We accomplish this by ensuring that veterans and their families can access the full range of benefits available to them; fighting for the interests of America’s injured heroes on Capitol Hill; and educating the public about the great sacrifices and needs of veterans transitioning back to civilian life.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This mission is carried forward by:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
